1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
From where you are now,
you can see the church.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
It does not look
very old, right?

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:15,000
But the parish here
already existed

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,000
in the 17th century.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Documents say that in 1666

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
there was a wooden church
covered with clay.

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
At that time,
the Reformation happened.

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:40,000
It was a religious movement

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:45,000
that created
new Christian groups.

10
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:50,000
The number of Catholics
became much smaller.

11
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:55,000
By 1706,
the church was ruined.

12
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:00,000
By the late 1700s,
it was gone.

13
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Today we do not know
its exact place.

14
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:10,000
But one item survived.

15
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
A stone baptismal font.

16
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:20,000
It was likely used
in the first church.

17
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:25,000
When the church disappeared,
the parish ended.

18
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Pęgów joined
the parish in Uraz.

19
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:35,000
People walked
several kilometers

20
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:40,000
to Sunday Mass.

21
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:45,000
This lasted until 1952,

22
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:50,000
when Pęgów joined
the parish in Szewce.

23
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Church was closer then,

24
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:00,000
because a palace
was used as a church.

25
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,000
But it still was
not perfect.

26
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:10,000
So in 1977,
construction began.

27
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:15,000
This was the current church.

28
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:20,000
It was a hard time
for building churches.

29
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Work lasted until 1984.

30
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
In 1985,
the parish returned.

31
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Since then,
it has worked independently.